works.description: Spring auction season began lately with a $170 million sale of Impressionist and modern art at Sotheby’s in New York and now, Christie’s International has sold $156 million worth of Impressionist and modern art on Wednesday. The sales total fell short of the presale expectation of $162.3 million. Both Sotheby’s and Christie’s have more or less failed to impress this year, and have started with a rather uninspiring performance.
